This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring March 25, 2012, as Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy. The proclamation highlights the historical ties between Greece and the United States, emphasizing the influence of ancient Greek democracy on the formation of American government. It also recognizes the contributions of Greek Americans to American society and the strong bond between the two nations. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.